<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The most slender and extremely elongated species (1.9-4.9 mm; 3.85-4.75
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide) occurring in Southeast Asia. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schedl" authorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Streptocranus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Streptocranus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Streptocranus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by its unique subquadrate and laterally constricted pronotum (type a in lateral view; type c in dorsal view) with a flat and long pronotal disc; elytral apex divaricate and ornamented with a pair of distal processes; protibiae slender, sickle-shaped; mycangial tufts absent; scutellum flat, flush with elytra; and procoxae contiguous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
