</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Only occurring in the Paleotropics and Oceania.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="gallery system">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Gallery system.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The gallery systems of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schedl" authorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Streptocranus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Streptocranus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Streptocranus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seem to be rather variable, with a few branches that may run horizontally or longitudinally, and may be irregularly widened, but without distinct brood chambers (
<bibRefCitation author="Browne, FG" journalOrPublisher="Malayan Forest Records" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 255" refId="B70" refString="Browne, FG, 1961b. The biology of Malayan Scolytidae and Platypodidae. Malayan Forest Records 22: 1 - 255" title="The biology of Malayan Scolytidae and Platypodidae." volume="22" year="1961 b">Browne 1961b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
